<HEADLINE> 19 More Die in Rains in North India State, Toll Up to 321 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Nineteen people, including
six women and four children, died in rain-related incidents,
mostly house collapses, on Friday in north India's Uttar Pradesh
state, the Press Trust of India (PTI) reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
This has brought the death toll in floods and other rain-
related incidents across Uttar Pradesh in the current monsoon
season up to 321, the PTI quoted local official reports as saying.
</P>
<P>
According to the local meteorological office, heavy rains were
likely to continue in several areas of the state in the next 24
hours. One of these areas, Faizabad, had already recorded a
maximum rainfall of 146 mm on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Rising waters in several rivers were posing threat to at least
six embankments, a local official spokesman was quoted as saying.
</P>
</TEXT>
