<HEADLINE> UAE to Provide Free Vaccinations for All Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The health minister of the
United Arab Emirate (UAE) announced Sunday that his ministry will
launch a campaign to provide free vaccinations to all students in
public and private schools.
</P>
<P>
Hamad Al Madfa made the announcement at a meeting with directors
of the ministry's School Health Departments and other health
officials, the official WAM news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The minister also called for intensified efforts to fight
smoking in schools and to prepare an effective awareness campaign
about the risks of smoking to the health of youths.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will, for the first time, carry out X-ray tests for
pupils at elementary schools, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the ministry will also study some other social
problems faced with teenagers in order to find solutions to them,
added the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
