<HEADLINE> Arafat to Visit Egypt for Negotiations With Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National Authority
Chairman Yasser Arafat is to visit Egypt on Monday for talks with
President Hosni Mubarak on the negotiations with Israel, the
Palestinian ambassador in Cairo said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Arafat will brief Mubarak on his meeting with U.S. President
Bill Clinton last Wednesday on ways of pushing forward the Mideast
peace process on the fringe of the U.N. Millennium Summit in New
York, Ambassador Zohdi al Qedra told Egypt's Middle East News
Agency.
</P>
<P>
He will also keep Mubarak posted on the decision taken by the
Palestinian Central Council (PCC) on the declaration of an
independent Palestinian state, al Qedra said.
</P>
<P>
After a two-day meeting, the PCC, the Palestinian mini-
parliament, agreed on Sunday not to declare statehood as initially
planned on September 13, and decided to meet again by November 15
to consider when the statehood declaration should be made.
</P>
<P>
Arafat's Monday visit will be the eighth to Egypt since the
Palestinian-Israeli Camp David summit ended on July 25 without an
agreement, largely due to the issue of Jerusalem, which both sides
claim as their capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
