<HEADLINE> 9 Killed, 5 Others Injured in Traffic Accident in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Nine people, including three
children, were killed and five others injured on Sunday when a
minibus plunged into a canal in southern Egypt, the Interior
Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The bus was passing through the city of Beni Suef, 120
kilometers south of capital Cairo, when a tire burst and driver
Kadhafi Mursi lost control of the vehicle, crashing into the
adjacent Ibrahimiya canal, the ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The injured were taken to a hospital in Beni Suef while rescue
workers managed to pull five of the nine dead bodies from the
canal, Egypt's Middle East News Agency quoted the statement as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The driver survived the accident, the statement said, without
giving the number of the passengers.
</P>
<P>
Traffic accidents are common in Egypt due to reckless driving.
Official figures show that over 3,000 people die each year in
traffic accidents, which also incur around 1 billion U.S. dollars
of economic losses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
