<HEADLINE> Ethiopian People Urged for Vigilance Against Drought, Famine  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian President
Negasso Gidada Sunday called on the people of the country to guard
against drought and famine, and to participate actively in anti-
HIV/AIDS campagne.
</P>
<P>
In his message made on the Ethiopian New Year's eve, Negasso
appealed to the public to rally behind the government to rid the
country once and for all from the scourge of drought and famine,
and to ensure Ethiopia's food self-sufficiency.
</P>
<P>
The president also attached importance to strengthening
national defense forces to ensure the sovereignty of the country.
</P>
<P>
Emphasizing the need for economic development in the effort to
free Ethiopia from under-development, Negaso urged the public to
make an all-out effort and called on local and foreign
entrepreneurs to intensify their investment activities towards
attaining that goal.
</P>
<P>
Among the areas, which will get maximum public and government
attention in the coming Ethiopian year, according to the president,
are HIV/AIDS and corruption.
</P>
<P>
He called upon the Ethiopian public to participate in anti-HIV/
AIDS activities sponsored by the National AIDS Council and other
organs at all level.
</P>
