<HEADLINE> 17 S. Leone Rebels Killed in Rescue Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 10 (Xinhua) Seventeen members of Sierra
Leone's rebels, the West Side Boys, were killed and their
commander captured when British troops freed seven hostages in a
military operation Sunday morning, said a source reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Sierra Leonean Information Minister Julius Spencer said in the
capital Freetown that 17 rebels were killed and 11 captured
including the commander, Brigadier-General Kallay, during Sunday's
military rescue operation.
</P>
<P>
The British troops attacked the base of the West Side Boys at
the Occra Hills to the east of Freetown and set free 7 hostages,
including 6 Britons and one Sierra Leonean, held by the rebels for
more than two weeks.
</P>
<P>
There had been casualties on both sides during the fighting,
said a senior British military officer, but declined to go into
details.
</P>
<P>
However, Sierra Leonean Military sources disclosed that one
British soldier had been seriously injured in the operation.
</P>
<P>
The abducted soldiers, including 11 Britons and one Sierra
Leonean, were taken hostage by the West Side Boys on August 25,
five Britons were later released. 
</P>
