<HEADLINE> Dalian Keeps Top Standings of China Soccer League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Dalian Shide has kept the top
standings of the Chinese first division soccer league after
drawing with Sichuan Quanxin 0-0 in Chengdu, capital of Sichuan
Province, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
After 22 round matches, Dalian totalled 46 point with 14
victories, four draws and four defeats.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Shenhua, only one point behind Dalian after the last
round, tied Tianjin Taida 1-1 in a home match. Shanghai Shenhua
opened the scoring in the 25th minute through Qi Hong. But Tianjin
's Zhang Xiaorui levelled the score in the 78th minute in a fast
counter-attack. Shanghai Shenhua amassed 45 points with 13 wins
and six draws.
</P>
<P>
With four round of competitions remaining, Dalian and Shanghai
will vie for the league title.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing Longxin whitewashed Jilin Aodong 7-1 tonight and
finished third with 37 points. The defending champions Shandong
Luneng drew with Beijing Guo'an 1-1 in a home game. Shandong has
now ranked fourth with 36 points.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's other matches, Liaoning Fushun tied Qingdao Hainiu
1-1, Shenzhen Ping'an edged Xiamen Xiaxin 4-0 and Yunnan Hongta
drew with Shenyang Haishi 2-2. 
</P>
