<HEADLINE> Three Gorges Residents Resettled in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The first group of over 800
Three Gorges residents arrived today in Jin'an County, in east
China's province of Jiangxi.
</P>
<P>
After a two-day journey by ship, the new comers, who had lived
for many years in the city of Chongqing, in the Three Gorges Area
on the upper reaches of the Yangtze River, settled down in their
new two-storey buildings.
</P>
<P>
Some 5,000 people are planned to arrive in Jiangxi in the next
three years, of which 2,200 will be resettled in Jin'an , said a
local official.
</P>
<P>
A dam is being built on the Three Gorges and it is scheduled to
be completed by 2003. As a result, a total of 70,000 local
residents have to be moved to other parts of China in seven years.
</P>
</TEXT>
