<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Tourism Market Full of Potential </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The tourism industry in China
will become a sector of great opportunity and high returns for
foreign investors, Sun Gang, Deputy Director of the State Tourism
Administration, said today.
</P>
<P>
He said at the fourth China Fair for International Investment
and Trade that China's tourism industry has at least five great
opportunities in the next two decades.
</P>
<P>
The first is that the Chinese government has listed tourism as
one of the growth factors of the economy.
</P>
<P>
The second is that local governments around China have given
priority to the development of tourism as a pillar industry of
local economies.
</P>
<P>
The third is due to the rich tourism resources in the western
part of the country becoming more open as the Chinese government
implements the strategy to develop west China.
</P>
<P>
The fourth involves the tourism sector increasingly open to
foreign investment following China's accession to the World Trade
Organization.
</P>
<P>
The fifth is that the rapid growth of the global tourism
industry will boost the Chinese tourism market.
</P>
<P>
By 1999, China became the fifth largest destiny for overseas
travelers and the seventh largest earner of tourist revenue in
terms of foreign exchange.
</P>
<P>
Over the first seven months of the year, China scored an 18.6
percent increase in foreign exchange earnings from tourism over
the same period last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
