<HEADLINE> Xiamen to Hold Exports-to-Taiwan Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Xiamen city in east China's
Fujian province will hold the fifth Exports to Taiwan Fair and the
Cross-Straits Commodities Fair from April 12 to 15, 2001.
</P>
<P>
The fairs will be jointly guided by the Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation, the Taiwan Affairs Office under
the State Council and the provincial government of Fujian. They
will be hosted by the machinery and electronics industrial
associations from both sides of the straits and the city
government of Xiamen and companies from Taiwan. 
</P>
