federal agencies, pushing the national budget to record levels.
Top Republicans predict a federal budget for the 2001 fiscal year
allowing at least $614 billion for discretionary spending,
exceeding a ceiling set in April.
</P>
<P>
-- Danes face a referendum to decide whether to preserve the
krone and their status or follow 12 other states of the 15-member
European Union in abandoning their money for a shared currency,
the euro. 
