<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Olympic Team Leaves for Sydney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- A six-member Bangladesh
contingent left here for Sydney Sunday to take part in the 27th
Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh will take part in three disciplines including
athletics, swimming and shooting. Mahbubul Alam and Fouzia Huda
will take part in the track and field event, Doly Akthar and Karar
Samedul Islam will be the two swimmers while Sabrina Sultana will
be the lone shooter to accompany the team
</P>
