<HEADLINE> Turkish President Briefs on U.N. Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Ahmet Necdet
Sezer said on Sunday that the globalization has promised new
opportunities for the humanity, but careful attention should be
paid not to make the rich richer and the poor poorer.
</P>
<P>
Outlining the points he made during the just-concluded United
Nations Millennium Summit, Sezer said, "I considered the trust in
people's will and the respect for law as important values."
</P>
<P>
Sezer made the remarks in a press conference at the Esenboga
Airport in Ankara upon his return from New York, where he attended
the U.N. summit.
</P>
<P>
"In my speech at the summit, I said that we should make civil
society to play a more important role in protecting democracy
against all extremist movements and fanaticism, and enlarging
democracy's limits," he said.
</P>
<P>
"I noted that democratization and economic development were
parallel processes. We should prioritize education of the youth,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
Sezer also called for a U.N. reform in order to make it more
transparent, and equip it with means that are necessary to protect
peace and stability. "I noted that poverty was the main reason of
instability in the world and more sources should be allocated for
social and economic programs in the developing countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day summit, Sezer also held bilateral talks
with a total of 24 heads of state and government, including United
States President Bill Clinton. 
</P>
