<P>
He declined to say where the British troops came from to launch
the attack.
</P>
<P>
BBC said the freed hostages might now be safe aboard a Royal
Fleet Auxiliary vessel at Freetown, the capital of Sierra Leone, a
former British colony in west Africa.
</P>
<P>
The British Defense Ministry declined to confirm this and said
more details would be provided at a news conference later in the
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
On August 25, a rebel group in Sierra Leone seized 11 British
soldiers and an officer of the Sierra Leone Army. It had freed
five of the hostages after Britain agreed to offer them some
equipment and food.
