<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets Turkish Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu
Jintao said here today that China places great importance on
developing friendship and cooperation with Turkey, and is willing
to work with Turkey to further promote cooperation between the two
countries and their armed forces in a variety of areas.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission, made
the remarks in a meeting this afternoon with Turkish Defense
Minister Sabahattin Cakmakoglu.
</P>
<P>
He said that the peoples of the two countries have a time-
honored friendship and bilateral relations have witnessed some new
progress in recent years thanks to joint efforts. He added that
Chinese President Jiang Zemin's successful visit to Turkey in
April this year defined the direction for establishing and
developing a trans-century and new cooperative partnership between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The joint crackdown on national separatism, international
terrorism and religious extremism as well as organized
transnational crimes is in the interests of the two countries and
peoples, and will also be of importance to safeguarding
tranquillity, stability and development in the region, the Chinese
vice-president said.
</P>
<P>
Cakmakoglu said that Sino-Turkish relations have been
developing smoothly since the establishment of diplomatic ties in
1971, and Turkey attaches great importance to promoting
cooperation with China, adding that the growth of bilateral
relations accords with the interests of both sides.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that the Turkish government will continue to
pursue the one-China policy. 
</P>
