<HEADLINE> Sheep Production Contributes 470 Million U.S. Dollars to Pak Annually </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's sheep production
annually contributes about Rs. 25 billion (about 470 million U.S.
dollars) to the country's economy, Associated Press of Pakistan
reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The country's sheep industry produces about 300,000 tons of
meat and 50,000 tons of wool each year, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Quoting their official sources at Jaba Livestock Production
Station, the report said that sheep are very important for socio-
economic reasons and command high prices during the main religious
festivals, particularly Eid-ul-Azha (The Sacrifice Festival of
Muslim). The majority of sheep in Pakistan, said the report, are
raised by flock owners with no or little land resources. The
feeding of the sheep is based on rangelands, natural pastures and
roadsides. 
</P>
