<HEADLINE> APEC Finance Ministers Ask for Stabilized Oil Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bandar Seri Begawan, September 10 (Xinhua) -- APEC finance
ministers Sunday stressed the need for stabilizing oil prices at
sustainable levels.
</P>
<P>
Ministers of the 21 APEC member economies at their 7th meeting
noted the risk posed by oil price volatility to the world economic
recovery and for developing countries that are heavily dependent
on oil market conditions, Abdul Rahman Taib, Brunei Industry and
Primary Resources Minister and lead chair of the meeting said at a
press conference at the end of the two-day meeting here.
</P>
<P>
He said that in light of rising world demand, the ministers
called for appropriate increases in supplies and other necessary
measures to promote long-term price stability in the mutual
interests of consumers and producers.
</P>
<P>
He added that the ministers also discussed measures to ensure
the sustainable growth necessary for increased economy prosperity
in the region and resolved to continue to pursue sound economic
and financial policies and structural reforms necessary to sustain
the momentum of economic growth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
