<HEADLINE> Canada Takes First Gold Medal for Green Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Canada has won the first gold
medal at the Millennium Olympics as they are the most
conscientious for recycling at the Sydney Olympic Games, said the
Olympic Village Newspaper on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian athletes in the Olympic village have been the most
conscientious so far in separating leftover food and other
materials for recycling after meals in the main dining hall, the
newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Cuba was ranked second, ahead of Spain and Yugoslavia, as the
latters tied in the bronze medal position, according to ratings
compiled by volunteers in the dining hall.
</P>
<P>
"Judges are looking for precision in putting the cutlery in the
correct tray, followed by concerted efforts to put food scraps,
paper and recyclable milk cartons and aluminium cans in their
allocated bins," the newspaper said. 
</P>
