<HEADLINE> Reactor Shuts Down Accidentally at Russian Nuke Power Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The No. 3 reactor shut down
automatically Sunday at a nuclear power plant in central Russia
due to unknown reasons, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The shutdown at the Beloyarskaya plant followed a sharp change
in the electric current frequency in the energy system, Interfax
said, quoting a spokesman with the Ministry for Emergencies.
</P>
<P>
The incident poses no threat to human being and the
environment because the safety system is operating reliably, said
plant Director Oleg Sarayev.
</P>
<P>
The radiation levels are normal in the town, according to the
Ministry for Emergencies.
</P>
<P>
A commission of the Russian State Inspection Department is
investigating the causes of the shutdown. Resumption of the No. 3
reactor's operation must have the commission's authorization.
