<HEADLINE> SW Provinces Enhance Cooperation in Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Three provinces, two
autonomous regions and two cities are joining hands for economic
take-off, China Daily's Business Weekly reported today.
</P>
<P>
They have vowed to intensify their co-operation to boost the
development of the vast western areas during an ongoing conference
on economy co-ordination.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from Yunnan, Sichuan, Guizhou, Guangxi, Tibet,
and Chengdu and Chongqing have also discussed the opening of
markets in the southwestern China.
</P>
<P>
The meeting focuses on joint efforts to improve the investment
environment by accelerating the construction of telecommunications
and transportation facilities and other infastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
The provinces, autonomous regions and cities also expect
cooperation on strengthening the protection and construction of
the environment along the upper reaches of the Yangtze River in
order to maintain sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
Since the first such conference was held in 1984, cooperation
in the region has been intensified. More than 17,000 projects,
which involved more than 65 billion yuan (about 7.8 billion U.S.
dollars) investment have been completed jointly by provinces and
cities in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
During the last 15 years, a transportation network including 64
highways with a total length of 1,500 km, a railway from Nanning
to Kunming and 160 airlines have been launched in southwestern
China.
</P>
<P>
Joint efforts have also been made in the development of natural
resources, the energy industry and tourism. 
