<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Border police Saturday
confiscated from an Indian vehicle four quintals of hemp at a
local market in Mahottari district bordering India, The Kathmandu
Post said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
An India-plated jeep laden with hemp worth 7 million rupees (10,
000 U.S.dollars) was seized along with the smugglers, a border
police officer was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
But all smugglers managed to run away when the police clashed
with a local mafia, said the policeman.
</P>
<P>
The local mafia gang attempted to set fire on the jeep carrying
the hemp in a bid to destroy the first-hand evidence, he said.
</P>
<P>
Police opened four rounds of fire in the air to bring the
situation under control, he added.
</P>
<P>
This is believed to be the first time that the border police
have been able to seize such a large chunk of hemp in Mahottari
district, a notorious district in Nepal for hemp-farming. 
</P>
