<HEADLINE> Nepali Girls Rescued From being Trafficked for Prostitution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Nine Nepalese girls have
been rescued from being trafficked to India for prostitution, The
Kathmandu Post said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The girls, between age of 14 to 25, were rescued at the Nepal-
India border point in Kakarbhitta in eastern Nepal by Maiti Nepal,
a non-governmental organization active in rescuing trafficked
girls, the English daily said.
</P>
<P>
The rescued girls said they were lured by the agents on the
pretext of getting them married or obtaining jobs for them in
India.
</P>
<P>
However, they will be sold to brothels through agents once in
India, Deepa Luitel, an employee of Maiti Nepal, was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The concerned district police are trying to locate such crime
agents in the border area, the daily said.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 5,000 to 7,000 Nepali girls are annually sold into
brothels in India for prostitution. 
