</P>
<P>
Boxing official Gafur Rakhimov of Uzbekistan and International
Baksetball Federation vice-president Carl Ching of Hong Kong,
China were refused entry last week for the Sydney Olympics opening
next Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to a Reuter's report on Sunday, Samaranch said that
he did not contest the Australian government's decision.
</P>
<P>
"We accept the decision," he said. "We have to trust and we
trust the Australian government."
</P>
<P>
Samaranch confirmed he had received a letter from Prime
Minister John Howard reaffirming the government's stance.
</P>
<P>
In the letter dated September 9, Howard said the pair had been
banned "after consideration of a number of factors including both
commitments in relation to the Olympic Charter and concerns
relating to the safety and security of the Australian community".
</P>
<P>
"The paramount consideration in decisions to refuse entry has
been the safety and security of the Australian community," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
