<HEADLINE> Thai Government Makes Minor Cabinet Reshuffle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 10 (Xinhua) -- King of Thailand Bhumibol
Adulyadej has approved the appointment of three new cabinet
ministers, which were earlier submitted by Thai Prime Minister
Chuan Leekpai, the Thai News Agency (TNA) reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The three new cabinet ministers are: Deputy Prime Minister,
Deputy Commerce Minister, and Minister of University Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Suthas Nguen-muen, who is now Justice Minister, was appointed
new Deputy Prime Minister concurrently, replacing Bhitchai
Rattakuk, who was lifted to be new President of Parliament, Rak
Tantisunthorn was appointed new Deputy Commerce Minister, and
Suchon Champhunot was appointed new Minister of University Affairs,
replacing Prachuab Chaiyasarn, who was ousted from the Chat
Pattana Party after he was invited to be new leader of the
Seridharm Party.
</P>
<P>
The appointment was immediately effective after the endorsement
of the King on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Visanu Krue-ngam, Secretary-General to the cabinet was quoted
as saying that the three new ministers were expected to be taken
oaths before His Majesty the King by September 13.
</P>
<P>
This minor cabinet reshuffle is believed to be the last of its
kind of the three-year Chuan Administration, as the Prime Minister
has planned to dissolve the parliament for general election by
next month, after the passage of key bills, including the 2001
budget bill and the amended election law, the report noted.
</P>
