<HEADLINE> Mexico's Popocatepetl Volcano Shows Signs of Activity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Popocatepetl volcano
in central Mexico spewed water steam and gases again on Saturday,
said the Interior Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The Interior Ministry's Disaster Prevention National Center (
Cenapred) said there were also some episodes of tremor of brief
duration and small intensity.
</P>
<P>
The volcanic alert semaphore continues in yellow and the
recommendation of not getting nearer than seven kilometers from
the volcano was repeated.
</P>
<P>
The volcano alternately spewed ashes or steam recently, which
made Cenapred to watch continuously its activities during this
time of the year.
</P>
<P>
Popocatepetl is situated some 80 kilometers southeast of Mexico
City. 
</P>
