<HEADLINE> Brazilian Coach Luxemburgo to Face Tax Trial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAO PAULO, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Brazil soccer manager
Wanderley Luxemburgo is facing trial for allegedly evading taxes
between 1993 and 1997, according to local paper Folha de S.Paulo
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Justice in Rio de Janeiro agreed on Friday to
process charges filed by the federal attorney general's office
that accused Luxemburgo of dishonestly concealing his income to
tax authorities, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
If convicted Luxemburgo, who is in Australia coaching Brazil's
Olympic soccer squad, could face a jail sentence of between two
and five years.
</P>
<P>
Federal criminal judge Valeria Caldi Magalhaes will also try
Luxemburgo's former business associate Renata Moura Alves on tax
concealment charges.
</P>
<P>
The case will be heard on October 16. 
