</P>
<P>
"I think that while the grounds are firm like this, it's going
to be a problem for him. We need softer ground and he'll be OK.
</P>
<P>
"We'll have to wait and see for Wednesday, and we took him off
as a precaution to try and protect him for Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"But, hopefully, he will be all right."
</P>
<P>
United's win takes them back to the top of the Premiership on
goal difference from Leicester City.
</P>
<P>
Paul Scholes opened the scoring in the 14th minute before
Fabien Barthez saved Niall Quinn's flick-on. Teddy Sheringham
doubled United's advantage and the impressive Scholes rifled home
the third seven minutes from time.
</P>
<P>
Ferguson was impressed with the quality of the goals, but not
the overall display.
</P>
<P>
He felt it might have been a different story if Barthez had not
saved Quinn's effort from Emerson Thome's header.
</P>
<P>
"I'm pleased with the result, but I didn't think the
performance was too great," he said.
</P>
<P>
"I thought the manner of the goals was fantastic and that was
the main feature for me.
</P>
<P>
"The first goal was an absolutely brilliant goal - the movement,
the cross from David and the finish.
</P>
<P>
"The second and third goals were maybe not as good, but were
still terrific goals.
</P>
<P>
"I think, though, the save from Barthez was vital because we
then went up the other end and scored the second goal. These
things win games."
</P>
<P>
Gerard Houllier admitted his relief at a last ditch 3-2 victory
over brave Manchester City at Anfield.
</P>
<P>
Two weeks ago, Liverpool led 3-0 at Southampton and caved in to
concede a point. And they almost suffered to same fate at City's
hands, the Maine Road team hitting back from two down to draw
level before Dietmar Hamann scored his second goal of the match to
clinch a desperate victory.
</P>
<P>
Houllier said: "At least this time we showed guts and character.
Manchester City were a real handful, particularly in the air.
</P>
<P>
"We dropped points at Southampton through lack of character,
this time it was our character that gave us our win.
</P>
<P>
"They play a direct way, but it suits them, and they are well
organised. The fact that they won at Leeds in midweek says
everything about them.
</P>
<P>
"They have a fine young 'keeper, in Steve Howey an experienced
defender and a hard working midfield. They've signed two
international quality strikers and, from what I've seen, they will
have no problem staying up."
</P>
<P>
He added: "As a neutral it was very entertaining, but as a
manager you can't be pleased with that, particularly when we
suffered as much as we did out there. But we did show guts, and
the fact that we are winning while not playing well, is important.
"
</P>
<P>
Arsenal boss Arsene Wenger suffered a nasty feeling of deja vu
at Valley Parad as his team dominated their encounter with
Bradford but had to settle for a point after a 1-1 draw.
</P>
<P>
Ashley Cole's first goal for the club levelled Stuart McCall's
10th-minute opener.
</P>
<P>
"It is just like the Sunderland game where we had chance after
chance," said Wenger.
</P>
<P>
"It is a bit frustrating because we played very well but we
showed great spirit to keep going.
</P>
<P>
"At least here we didn't lose but it is another of those games
we should have won."
</P>
<P>
Despite his team's dominance, Wenger knew the Gunners could
easily have been beaten had Benito Carbone not smashed a glorious
chance over the bar with 13 minutes remaining.
</P>
<P>
"Bradford did very well and they had us in trouble with long
balls, corners and free-kicks and we didn't take our chances.
</P>
<P>
"Thierry Henry did well but it is difficult to come back from 1-
0 down away from home."
</P>
<P>
Under-fire Chelsea boss Gianluca Vialli was full of praise for
his players after they bounced back from the disappointment of
surrendering two points to Arsenal in midweek with a 0-0 draw away
to Newcastle.
</P>
<P>
"We came here to get the three points and the way we played, I
think, showed that," he said. "Newcastle played very well.
</P>
<P>
"It was wide open. Both teams tried their best to win the match,
so that was a good attitude for a team that has been under fire
for the last three days.
</P>
<P>
"We showed that composure and confidence. We could have won it,
we could have lost it - it was a cracking football match."
</P>
</TEXT>
